Hilary Putnam awarded The Rolf Schock Prize
%%%
<p>
The Rolf Schock Prize in Logic and Philosophy 2011 is being awarded by 
the Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences to Hilary Putnam "for his 
contribution to the understanding of semantics for theoretical and 
'natural kind' terms, and of the implications of this semantics for 
philosophy, theory of knowledge, philosophy of science and metaphysics". 
For further information see 
<a href="http://kva.se/en/pressroom/Press-releases-2011/Hilary-Putnam-is-being-awarded-The-Rolf-Schock-Prize-in-Logic-and-Philosophy-2011/" rel="external">the official press release</a>.
</p>
